<p>The <abbr title="Office for Budget Responsibility">OBR</abbr>’s ‘Economic and Fiscal Outlook’ shows that the government is forecast to meet the fiscal rules set out above in section 1.12. There is a current budget surplus of £11.7 billion in 2022-23, providing headroom against this rule. Net investment is expected to average 2.9% of <abbr title="Gross Domestic Product">GDP</abbr> over 2020-21 to 2024-25 – below the 3% target – while the debt interest to revenue ratio remains below 6%.</p>

